was so sorry for him that I forgot to be sorry for 
myself. At last I sat down to rest on a sofa giv 
ing a pretty view of the lawn and the house; and 
Mr. Stone took post beside me like a sentinel. 
Then a loophole of escape for himself and for me 
(I suppose) suggested itself; he asked me suddenly 
if I would not like some refreshment ? I hesitated, 
and he went on to say eagerly, there was a refreshment tent on the lawn at the other side of the 
house. I was as glad as he was to know it ; and 
