"Thorns and thistles too!" said I. 

"Thorns and thistles too; as things are." 

" As things are ? " 

"Yes. I mean, with sin in the world." 

"Mr. Iredell, have you travelled also in warm 
countries? in the East?" 

"Yes, much." 

"And found the people not so good?" 

" We must beware of hasty judgments. Before 

one race can be compared fairly with another, very 
many things must be taken account of. Not only 
mountains and glaciers, or the absence of them; 
but religion, government, and education. In any 
case however, climate has a great deal to do. An 
Oriental bazar would be simply impossible in a cold 
